**India's Navy Accidentally Reveals Removal of Nuclear Weapons in Yoga Post on Instagram**
The Indian Navy accidentally revealed the removal of nuclear weapons from a ship in a yoga post on Instagram. The Federation of American Scientists (FAS) used social media to track the movement of India's nuclear arsenal. According to Matt Korda, Associate Director of the Nuclear Information Project at FAS, 'This is probably the most unexpected source I've found for information related to nuclear weapons.' Korda discovered that India had removed its nuclear weapons from two patrol boats, the INS Suvarna and the INS Subhadra, by reviewing satellite images and searching for keywords on social media. The removal of the nuclear weapons was confirmed by two yoga posts on Instagram, one from October 2022 and another from February 2024, which showed the absence of the stabilizers required for launching nuclear missiles. 'It's a bit unusual to learn about military systems, especially nuclear systems, in non-military environments,' Korda said. 'This case is unique because it shows that even in a non-military context, information about nuclear systems can be revealed.' 
