The United States has revealed the number of its strategic nuclear warheads, which stood at 3,748 as of September 2023. This is the first time the data has been made public since October 2021. The Federation of American Scientists stated that the nuclear arsenal will consist of 3,708 warheads in 2024. Additionally, the number of non-strategic (tactical) nuclear weapons in the US has decreased by more than 90% since September 1991. According to the National Nuclear Security Administration, the US had 3,748 nuclear warheads intended for strategic forces as of September 2023.
