**US Reveals Data on Strategic Nuclear Arsenal, Russia and US Remain World's Largest Nuclear Powers**
The United States has revealed data on its strategic nuclear arsenal, stating that it has 3748 nuclear warheads as of September 2023. This is the first time the US has provided such information since October 2021. The US National Nuclear Security Administration (NNSA) reported that between 1994 and 2023, Washington has dismantled 12,088 nuclear warheads. Additionally, around 2000 warheads are currently being decommissioned. The US has reduced its non-strategic (tactical) nuclear arsenal by more than 90% since September 30, 1991. The NNSA emphasized the importance of transparency in nuclear arsenals for efforts to prevent the spread and disarmament of nuclear weapons, including obligations under the Nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty. Russia and the US remain the world's largest nuclear powers, accounting for around 90% of the world's nuclear arsenal. The US has deployed nuclear weapons in five NATO countries under the protection of the US Air Force, with a total of around 100 warheads, consisting entirely of gravity bombs B61. The US regularly speaks about the nuclear threat posed by other countries, including Russia's alleged plans to deploy similar weapons in space. Russia's Foreign Minister Sergey Lavrov has denied these allegations, stating that they are baseless and have no connection to reality. US Secretary of State Antony Blinken has stated that Iran is close to being able to obtain materials for making nuclear weapons, saying it's a matter of weeks.
